pillars of oops
- encapsulation - change height method()
- polymorphism - ability to perform differently at different situations
- inheritance
- abstraction - show only required thing and hide unwanted thing to the user (Binding attribute and method)

why -oop
- better organization
- easy modularity
- Scalability of the code

access modifiers
only written in side the class but not in method.

private - can only used inside the class eg inside class's method
protected - can use only inside the packages , different classes which is under the same package
public - can use in different packages


inheritance-
is a - relationship child -> parent
has a  - relationship  parent -> child



